    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1061"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1061">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3613.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName type="from">Pascual Orozco</persName> to the <gloss type="to"
                            >President</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso, Texas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Fountain was executed because he was fighting us, handling a rapid-firing machine
                    in Villa ranks. It was done without consideration what nationality he was. We
                    want the strongest possible friendship with your wonderful people and have no
                    prejudices against them. We mail you full explanation in the matter and feel
                    confident you would approve it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pascual Orozco.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
